    "body": "@ajsantander: Not sure how to do that here. The `Create pull request` option is disabled, with `Choose different branches or forks above to discuss and review changes` appearing next to it.\r\n\r\nThe code for this functionality is already given above, and the test is provided hereby:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    let ONE = web3.toBigNumber(1);\r\n    let TWO = web3.toBigNumber(2);\r\n\r\n    for (let n = 0; n < 256; n++) {\r\n        it(`test:`, async () => {\r\n            try {\r\n                let retVal = await safeMath.shl.call(ONE, web3.toBigNumber(n));\r\n                assert(n < 255 && retVal.equals(TWO.toPower(n)), `test passed when it should have failed`);\r\n            }\r\n            catch (error) {\r\n                assert(n == 255, `test failed when it should have passed`);\r\n            }\r\n        });\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'd be happy to submit it myself, but I will need some specific instructions on how to do it here.\r\n\r\nThanks\r\n\r\nUPDATE:\r\n\r\nI ended up submitting it, though not entirely sure that I have reconciled with the guidelines for this (branch name, etc).",
