    "body": "Left shift on uints can be emulated with multiplication by a power of 2.  I haven't tested if it's faster in EVM or not.  According to the [yellow paper](https://github.com/ethereum/yellowpaper), multiplication is Wlow (5 gas); shifting might be Wverylow (3 gas) but there doesn't actually appear to be an EVM command for it. \r\n\r\nSome use cases are [here](https://stackoverflow.com/q/520625/798371) but in all cases where I've used left-shift, it's been either (a) not a case where SafeMath would be needed because I wasn't working with representations of numbers, or (b) a shortcut way of doing multiplication. \r\n\r\n\r\n",
